from bjone brad jone subject re gun in backcountry no thank in article john k gever write do anybody read thi group have an actual honest-to-god experience with violent crime in the backcountry to tell about it wa around in the shenandoah valley near woodstock virginium me my wife a friend hi wife and hi kid be hike in a totally desolate mountain area all of a sudden large rock begin rain down on u looking up we saw at least punk gleefully let loose rock from what wa an obviou stash they be a couple hundred foot above u meanwhile the woman and kid be scream and run for cover and the punk be shriek with laughter me and my friend yell for them to knock it off they respond that we should get me and my friend draw my pistol and fire a couple of time into the tree above their head they run with no more pound rock come at my head we proceed on my journey sorry but me and my friend saw no need to let it evolve to a more violent level than we be already experience i gues we should have try harder to understand and cope with the anger that society have instill in them and wa drive them to do such thing gues that a cro i have to bear brad 